  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HCFC Phase-Out Management Plan (Stage I)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HCFC PHASE-OUT MANAGEMENT PLAN (STAGE I) Part I of the project is being submitted to the Multilateral Fund for funding to ensure reduction of HCFC consumption by 35% by 1st January 2020. Part II, whose detailed activities will be formulated at a later stage, will allow for the total phase out of HCFCs in Burkina Faso by 1st January 2030, save for the service tail of 2.5%. The strategy in the HPMP is based building of national capacity to achieve the phase out as well as on economic instruments and incentives, and on the strengthening of ODS regulations</narrative>
  </description>
